subsection.def:
alteration (改動),
                for the purposes of the definition of constructed, means any repair,
                alteration or modification that is of a major character; (L.N. 255 of 2018)

paragraph.text:
constructed of suitable non-combustible materials and all materials whose
                        use is necessary for or ancillary to its construction and erection shall be
                        non-combustible;

paragraph.content:
construction identifiable with the ship begins and assembly of the ship
                        has commenced comprising at least 50 tonnes or 1% of the estimated mass of
                        all structural material, whichever is less;

subsection.def:
draught
                    (吃水) means the vertical distance from the
                moulded base line amidships to a subdivision load waterline;

paragraph.content:
in relation to Part VIA, the equipment used for the preparation of oil
                        fuel for delivery to the oil burners of an oil-fired boiler and includes the
                        oil pressure pumps, filters and heaters;

assembly of the ship has commenced comprising at least 50 tonnes or 1%
                        of the estimated mass of all structural material, whichever is
                        less;

subsection.def:
suitable
                    (適合) in relation to material means approved
                by the Director as suitable for the purpose for which it is used;

paragraph.content:
all communication equipment, fire detecting systems and signals which may
                    be required in an emergency, if they are electrically operated from the ship’s
                    main generating sets;

open deck spaces and enclosed promenades forming lifeboat and liferaft
                    embarkation and lowering
                    stations);

private sanitary facilities shall be considered part of the accommodation
                    space in which they are
                    located);

auxiliary machinery spaces, other than those in categories (10) and (11),
                    which contain internal combustion machinery or other oil-burning, heating or
                    pumping units;

subparagraph.content:
separated from the stairway enclosure by the provision of “A” Class
                            divisions in accordance with regulation
                            55;

paragraph.content:
ducts not less than 0.075 square metres in sectional area and all vertical
                    ducts serving more than a single between-deck space shall be constructed of
                    steel or other equivalent material;

adequate
                arrangements shall be made to permit the release of smoke in the event of
                fire;

windows
                shall not be fitted in machinery space
                casings;

a stairway which is enclosed only at one level shall be regarded as part of
                    the space from which it is not separated by a fire
                    door);

lockers and storerooms having areas of less than 4 square metres, drying
                    rooms and
                    laundries);

machinery spaces as defined in regulation 1 but do not include
                    machinery spaces of Category
                    A);

all spaces used for cargo (including cargo oil tanks) and trunkways and
                    hatchways to such spaces, other than special category
                    spaces);

open deck spaces, enclosed promenades containing no fire risk, and the
                    space outside superstructures and
                    deckhouses);

furniture
                    in the corridors and stairway enclosures shall be kept to a
                    minimum;

subparagraph.content:
an automatic fire alarm and fire detection system of an approved type
                        shall be provided unless an efficient continuous patrol system is
                        maintained;

manual fire alarms shall be provided throughout the special category
                        spaces and one shall be placed close to each exit from such spaces;
                        and

separated from the stairway enclosure by the provision of “A” Class
                            divisions in accordance with regulation
                            55;

in ships carrying not more than 36
                        passengers—7
                        metres;

in ships carrying more than 36
                        passengers—13
                        metres;

paragraph.content:
additional subdivision is provided in way of the step to maintain
                            the same measure of safety as that secured by a plane bulkhead;
                            or

subparagraph.content:
transverse extent: 20% of the breadth of the ship, measured inboard
                            from the ship’s side at right angles to the centre line at the level of
                            the deepest subdivision load waterline;

for a ro/ro passenger ship—throughout the ship’s length;
